#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Dasabalavagga"
msgstr "3. The Ten Powers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Dutiyadasabalasutta"
msgstr "22. The Ten Powers (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.22:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Dasabalasamannāgato, bhikkhave, tathāgato catūhi ca vesārajjehi samannāgato "
"āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a Realized One has ten powers and four kinds of self-assurance. "
"With these he claims the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the "
"assemblies, and turns the holy wheel."

# Note how MS attempts to make sense of this sutta by inserting punctuation; a colon or an em-dash after the initial statement. Now, unlike the previous, it inserts quotes here, suggesting that this passage is meant to be a quote; but the quote is closed below on “nirodho hoti”, and there is no ’ti, so this is unjustified.
msgctxt "sn12.22:1.3"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ iti rūpassa samudayo iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo, "
msgstr "Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form. "

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.4"
msgid "iti vedanā iti vedanāya samudayo iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo, "
msgstr ""
"Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of "
"feeling. "

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.5"
msgid "iti saññā iti saññāya samudayo iti saññāya atthaṅgamo, "
msgstr ""
"Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of "
"perception. "

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.6"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo, "
msgstr ""
"Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of "
"choices. "

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.7"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ iti viññāṇassa samudayo iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo."
msgstr ""
"Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the "
"ending of consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.8"
msgid "Iti imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati;"
msgstr "When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises."

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.9"
msgid "imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that "
"ceases. That is:"

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.10"
msgid "Yadidaṃ avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "Ignorance is a condition for choices."

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.11"
msgid "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Choices are a condition for consciousness. …"

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.12"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.13"
msgid "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho;"
msgstr ""
"When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease."

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.14"
msgid "saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When choices cease, consciousness ceases. …"

msgctxt "sn12.22:1.15"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti’."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.22:2.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko."
msgstr ""
"So the teaching has been well explained by me, made clear, opened, "
"illuminated, and stripped of patchwork."

msgctxt "sn12.22:2.2"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ svākkhāte kho, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite "
"chinnapilotike alameva saddhāpabbajitena kulaputtena vīriyaṃ ārabhituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Just this much is quite enough for someone who has gone forth out of faith "
"from a good family to rouse up their energy."

#. VAR: nhāru → nahāru (bj, s1-3, km) | nahārū (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.22:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘kāmaṃ taco ca nhāru ca aṭṭhi ca avasissatu, sarīre upassussatu "
"maṃsalohitaṃ. Yaṃ taṃ purisathāmena purisavīriyena purisaparakkamena "
"pattabbaṃ, na taṃ apāpuṇitvā vīriyassa saṇṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Gladly, let only skin, sinews, and tendons remain! Let the flesh and blood "
"waste away in my body! I will not stop trying until I have achieved what is "
"possible by manly strength, energy, and vigor.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.29"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.22:3.1"
msgid ""
"Dukkhaṃ, bhikkhave, kusīto viharati vokiṇṇo pāpakehi akusalehi dhammehi, "
"mahantañca sadatthaṃ parihāpeti."
msgstr ""
"A lazy person lives in suffering, mixed up with bad, unskillful qualities, "
"and ruins a great deal of their own good."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.2"
msgid ""
"Āraddhavīriyo ca kho, bhikkhave, sukhaṃ viharati pavivitto pāpakehi "
"akusalehi dhammehi, mahantañca sadatthaṃ paripūreti."
msgstr ""
"An energetic person lives happily, secluded from bad, unskillful qualities, "
"and fulfills a great deal of their own good."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.3"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, hīnena aggassa patti hoti."
msgstr "The best isn’t reached by the worst."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.4"
msgid "Aggena ca kho, bhikkhave, aggassa patti hoti."
msgstr "The best is reached by the best."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.5"
msgid "Maṇḍapeyyamidaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyaṃ, satthā sammukhībhūto."
msgstr ""
"This spiritual life is the cream, mendicants, and the Teacher is before you."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.6"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ ārabhatha appattassa pattiyā, anadhigatassa "
"adhigamāya, asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"So you should rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the "
"unachieved, and realizing the unrealized, thinking:"

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.7"
msgid "‘Evaṃ no ayaṃ amhākaṃ pabbajjā avañjhā bhavissati saphalā saudrayā."
msgstr ""
"‘In this way our going forth will not be wasted, but will be fruitful and "
"fertile."

# Note that these sentences appear in reverse order at AN 7.72
#. VAR: Yesañca → yesaṃ (bj, s1-3, km) | yesaṃ hi (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.22:3.8"
msgid ""
"Yesañca mayaṃ paribhuñjāma "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ tesaṃ te kārā "
"amhesu mahapphalā bhavissanti mahānisaṃsā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"And our use of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for "
"the sick shall be of great fruit and benefit for those who offered them.’"

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.9"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.10"
msgid ""
"Attatthaṃ vā hi, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Considering your own good, mendicants, is quite enough for you to persist "
"with diligence."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.11"
msgid ""
"paratthaṃ vā hi, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Considering the good of others is quite enough for you to persist with "
"diligence."

msgctxt "sn12.22:3.12"
msgid ""
"ubhayatthaṃ vā hi, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena "
"sampādetun”ti."
msgstr ""
"Considering the good of both is quite enough for you to persist with "
"diligence.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.22:3.13"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
